I see now. No, this is not possible with `traitlets`.

You could achieve the same effect by extending `Hastraits.__setattr__`:

```python

class OnlyTraits(HasTraits):

    def __setattr__(self, name, value):
    	if isinstance(getattr(type(self), name), TraitType):
    	    super(OnlyTraits, self).__setattr__(name, value)
   	else:
   	    raise AttributeError("%s objects have no trait "
   	        "name '%s'" % (type(self).__name__, name))
```

