This could be partially addressed by #453. However, this doesn't *fully* support recursive remote functions. For example, the PR does not fix the following example.

```python
def create_and_call_f():
  @ray.remote
  def f():
    return [f.remote()]

  f.remote()  

create_and_call_f()
```

Basically, you can't define a recursive remote function inside of another function or class. We'll have to look into how to do this properly.

